reviews.text: Called half hr before close and was delivered a fresh delicious pie! Their Brooklyn veggie with sausage is outstanding! Thanks!
As close to NYC style pizza that your going to get down here. Perfect cheese to dough ratio and the sauce is very good.

Good food but don't ever try to order delivery. Multiple times my driver got to the restaurant, waited 20-30 minutes and eventually dropped the order and left. So then I had to wait another 30+ minutes for another driver, because who just sits in east vineland doing doordash. I'm the first person to throw doordash under the bus, but every driver has gotten to the store quickly and messaged me about the wait. They're just legit never ready. Update the time frame you give the delivery apps or something. No other local mom and pop shop has this issue.
I was craving their white seafood pizza. It‚Äôs always delicious as is everything I‚Äôve ever ordered from this restaurant. Pizza crust is perfect and they are NOT stingy with toppings.

We have been going here for years. Lately, it seems as though the food and service has been declining.  We had to get our own menus because the waitress wasn't coming to our table.  I ordered an Italian hoagie wrap.  There were a couple pieces of meat and one piece of cheese on it.  The rest was filled with lettuce and salad dressing. I couldn't taste anything but the lettuce and dressing.  I then had to go to the counter to ask for a box because the waitress never came back to check if we needed anything else.

detailedReviews.author: Ryan Tuck
detailedReviews.text: I ordered a damn cheesesteak and had to wait over a half hour for it, meanwhile my girlfriend ordered 3 slices of pizza and got them immediately. Now, I get it, pizza just gets reheated and you actually have to cook the meat in the cheesesteak, I gave them the full benefit of the doubt the whole time. However, I asked them ‚Äúany word on how long for the cheesesteak‚Äù and what happened truly pissed me off beyond belief. They stashed it away hidden in the back and gave it to me cold. Everyone else who got take out got their food immediately. I sat down and patiently waited, and they spit on me by hiding my damn food and giving it to me cold. Even if they did say ‚Äúcheesesteak,‚Äù maybe they could have said it LOUDER over the people in the restaurant and leave it on the counter for me to grab when I see it‚Äôs done, rather than ME having to ask SOMEONE ELSE if it was done; the lady who took my order (then had a conversation with the couple behind me, so she wasn‚Äôt bound to the register) could have seen my impatience and told me it was done, but nope. The place spit on me, and a place that I normally do like to get food at screwed me over for literally no reason.
